1
00:00:58,542 --> 00:01:03,117
[Episode 10: Rudolph]

2
00:01:21,883 --> 00:01:23,549
Yeah.

3
00:01:23,549 --> 00:01:25,799
We just got to the hotel.

4
00:01:25,799 --> 00:01:27,083
<i>Writer Kim!</i>

5
00:01:27,083 --> 00:01:28,299
Yeah.

6
00:01:28,299 --> 00:01:30,966
We're at a pub, you should come.

7
00:01:30,966 --> 00:01:32,106
A pub?

8
00:01:32,106 --> 00:01:33,674
<i>Yeah.</i>

9
00:01:33,674 --> 00:01:36,299
It's not far from the hotel.

10
00:01:36,299 --> 00:01:37,917
Is that Writer Kim?

11
00:01:37,917 --> 00:01:40,208
Tell her to get over here.

12
00:01:40,208 --> 00:01:42,208
The Editor wants you here now.

13
00:01:42,208 --> 00:01:45,466
<i>- Here's your chicken.
- Come with PD Shin.</i>

14
00:01:45,466 --> 00:01:48,518
Sure, I'll check with him.

15
00:01:52,917 --> 00:01:54,341
Let's go.

16
00:01:54,341 --> 00:01:57,000
Drinks with Soon Rok, perfect chance to bond.

17
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,125
Yes!

18
00:01:58,125 --> 00:02:00,583
Chicken time!

19
00:02:00,583 --> 00:02:02,219
They said chicken's waiting for us!

20
00:02:02,219 --> 00:02:04,967
The 4th floor, that's where your room is.

21
00:02:06,133 --> 00:02:07,958
The Editor said

22
00:02:07,958 --> 00:02:10,341
he's at a beer place and wants us to come...

23
00:02:10,341 --> 00:02:13,125
You heading there? Let me take you.

24
00:02:13,125 --> 00:02:14,542
What about you?

25
00:02:14,542 --> 00:02:17,841
I've got some work to do, so...

26
00:02:17,841 --> 00:02:20,716
Once you're settled, I'll take you there.

27
00:02:20,716 --> 00:02:23,667
- Chicken, chicken!
- Why bother going if Soon Rok's not coming?

28
00:02:24,667 --> 00:02:27,958
Wait, no chicken?

29
00:02:27,958 --> 00:02:29,549
I'm pretty tired too,

30
00:02:29,549 --> 00:02:31,292
so I think I'll just rest.

31
00:02:31,292 --> 00:02:32,293
Are you sure?

32
00:02:32,293 --> 00:02:34,083
Just let them know I'm turning in

33
00:02:34,083 --> 00:02:36,341
and I'll catch up with them tomorrow.

34
00:02:36,341 --> 00:02:38,175
Sure.

35
00:02:39,083 --> 00:02:42,167
You don't want chicken?

36
00:02:42,167 --> 00:02:45,550
I do want chicken, but...

37
00:02:58,508 --> 00:03:00,800
<i>Going up.</i>

38
00:03:01,500 --> 00:03:05,258
<i>4th floor. Doors are closing.</i>

39
00:03:05,258 --> 00:03:07,208
Which floor are you...

40
00:03:07,208 --> 00:03:09,217
I'm on the same floor as you.

41
00:03:10,249 --> 00:03:12,333
I'm rooming with the Editor.

42
00:03:12,333 --> 00:03:13,833
For real?

43
00:03:13,833 --> 00:03:16,424
That can't be fun.

44
00:03:16,424 --> 00:03:18,925
Such is life at the bottom.

45
00:03:28,549 --> 00:03:31,250
Silence again.

46
00:03:31,250 --> 00:03:32,750
Isn't it strange?

47
00:03:32,750 --> 00:03:36,167
A few days back, I couldn't stand it,

48
00:03:36,167 --> 00:03:39,550
yet here it is, feeling so sweet.

49
00:03:41,583 --> 00:03:42,633
Let's go.

50
00:03:42,633 --> 00:03:44,467
Oh, okay.

51
00:03:54,833 --> 00:03:57,841
Well then, good night.

52
00:03:57,841 --> 00:04:00,342
Yes, great work today.

53
00:04:35,250 --> 00:04:38,133
<i>Sweet silence.</i>

54
00:04:38,133 --> 00:04:40,917
<i>I love how Soon Rok smells. What's his cologne?</i>

55
00:04:40,917 --> 00:04:45,424
<i>Does Soon Rok have natural curls?</i>

56
00:04:45,424 --> 00:04:48,500
<i>Soon Rok, ditch the glasses, get contacts!</i>

57
00:04:48,500 --> 00:04:52,133
<i>But it's Soon Rok's birthday.</i>

58
00:04:57,133 --> 00:05:00,050
<i>It's still his birthday.</i>

59
00:05:11,799 --> 00:05:14,542
<i>After being with him all day on his birthday,</i>

60
00:05:14,542 --> 00:05:16,258
<i>is it okay to just skip it?</i>

61
00:05:16,258 --> 00:05:17,299
Yeah.

62
00:05:17,299 --> 00:05:18,966
There was cake earlier, remember?

63
00:05:18,966 --> 00:05:22,008
<i>Please, that was Na Hui's cake.</i>

64
00:05:25,049 --> 00:05:27,883
Wouldn't sending a gift now be too late?

65
00:05:27,883 --> 00:05:31,549
<i>Staying quiet would look even stranger, no?</i>

66
00:05:31,549 --> 00:05:33,841
Right.

67
00:05:33,841 --> 00:05:35,924
Yeah, skipping it entirely would be odder.

68
00:05:35,924 --> 00:05:38,674
It looks like he's still mad.

69
00:05:38,674 --> 00:05:42,008
Keep it light so he won't feel pressured.

70
00:05:44,966 --> 00:05:46,800
Okay.

71
00:05:50,049 --> 00:05:53,049
Too cheap?

72
00:05:53,049 --> 00:05:54,925
Then...

73
00:05:58,174 --> 00:06:01,008
Oh, this one's better.

74
00:06:01,008 --> 00:06:03,841
But with perfume,

75
00:06:03,841 --> 00:06:06,466
if it's not his taste, he won't use it, right?

76
00:06:06,466 --> 00:06:09,091
This is a bit much.

77
00:06:09,091 --> 00:06:10,917
No, not this one.

78
00:06:10,917 --> 00:06:13,258
Wait, he's not much

79
00:06:13,258 --> 00:06:15,216
of a drinker though, is he?

80
00:06:15,216 --> 00:06:16,883
Wait, or does he drink?

81
00:06:16,883 --> 00:06:20,141
I'm so bad at choosing gifts.

82
00:06:26,875 --> 00:06:29,383
[What gift are you looking for?]
Wait, only ten minutes left till midnight?

83
00:06:29,383 --> 00:06:30,966
<i>Pick whatever.</i>

84
00:06:30,966 --> 00:06:33,841
<i>It's pointless if it's past twelve.</i>

85
00:06:33,841 --> 00:06:36,049
What do I even pick?

86
00:06:36,049 --> 00:06:37,133
Fine,

87
00:06:37,133 --> 00:06:41,175
this works best. It's simple.
Let's go with simple.

88
00:06:48,799 --> 00:06:52,042
<i>What if he's asleep
and you're just bothering him?</i>

89
00:06:52,042 --> 00:06:56,258
<i>Plus, isn't the Editor his roommate?</i>

90
00:06:56,258 --> 00:07:00,349
<i>What if the Editor spots it
and misreads the whole thing...</i>

91
00:07:01,133 --> 00:07:03,591
Actually...

92
00:07:03,591 --> 00:07:05,925
that's not a good idea.

93
00:07:16,924 --> 00:07:19,308
What a nice breeze.

94
00:07:26,375 --> 00:07:27,799
- It's PD Shin!
- It's PD Shin!

95
00:07:27,799 --> 00:07:29,883
He hasn't gone to bed yet.

96
00:07:29,883 --> 00:07:31,549
And the Editor's nowhere around!

97
00:07:31,549 --> 00:07:33,383
Now's our chance!

98
00:07:33,383 --> 00:07:34,731
What time is it?

99
00:07:34,731 --> 00:07:37,383
Three minutes to go. It's 11:57.

100
00:07:37,383 --> 00:07:40,516
- Yumi, let's do it now!
- Yumi, let's do it now!

101
00:07:44,174 --> 00:07:48,000
<i>Couldn't let it pass.</i>

102
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:50,050
<i>Happy birthday.</i>

103
00:07:51,758 --> 00:07:54,091
- Press it!
- Press it!

104
00:07:54,091 --> 00:07:56,050
Do it!

105
00:08:13,383 --> 00:08:15,425
- He's reading it now.
- He's reading it now.

106
00:08:24,833 --> 00:08:27,342
He's writing back.

107
00:08:30,091 --> 00:08:32,875
He's writing a really long reply!

108
00:08:32,875 --> 00:08:34,667
Hold on, he's erasing it?

109
00:08:34,667 --> 00:08:37,508
He must be thinking it over.

110
00:08:45,683 --> 00:08:47,983
Now he's writing it over.

111
00:09:04,958 --> 00:09:06,925
It came!

112
00:09:14,549 --> 00:09:16,299
What did he write?

113
00:09:16,299 --> 00:09:19,091
<i>Thank you. I'll enjoy it.</i>

114
00:09:19,091 --> 00:09:21,383
<i>Have a good night.</i>

115
00:09:22,591 --> 00:09:26,592
A smiley face!

116
00:09:29,508 --> 00:09:31,799
A smiley, everyone! Can you see it?

117
00:09:31,799 --> 00:09:33,383
- Yes, we can!
- Yes, we can!

118
00:09:33,383 --> 00:09:37,549
Nobody sends that to a person they hate.
Isn't that true?

119
00:09:37,549 --> 00:09:39,758
- Exactly!
- Exactly!

120
00:09:47,466 --> 00:09:51,500
<i>A moon shaped like a smile
lit up the village that night.</i>

121
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:53,508
Unbelievable.

122
00:09:58,375 --> 00:10:00,458
<i>This feeling is so nice.</i>

123
00:10:01,333 --> 00:10:05,208
<i>I forgot what this feeling was like.</i>

124
00:10:05,799 --> 00:10:10,008
<i>It's like my heart just melted.</i>

125
00:10:49,424 --> 00:10:50,841
Editor.

126
00:10:50,841 --> 00:10:53,083
Oh, Writer Kim!

127
00:10:53,083 --> 00:10:54,549
You're up early?

128
00:10:54,549 --> 00:10:57,258
Yeah, have a seat.

129
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:02,083
You didn't show up last night.

130
00:11:02,083 --> 00:11:05,008
I was completely wiped out yesterday.

131
00:11:05,008 --> 00:11:07,958
I seriously wanted to be there but no way...

132
00:11:07,958 --> 00:11:09,716
Smart move.

133
00:11:09,716 --> 00:11:11,133
You went hard

134
00:11:11,133 --> 00:11:12,258
last night, didn't you?

135
00:11:12,258 --> 00:11:15,049
No, I've really toned it down.

136
00:11:15,049 --> 00:11:18,125
I Da's been scolding me so much.

137
00:11:18,125 --> 00:11:19,883
She can be scary about that stuff.

138
00:11:19,883 --> 00:11:22,667
Oh, tell me about it.

139
00:11:22,667 --> 00:11:24,008
Would you like some coffee?

140
00:11:24,008 --> 00:11:26,299
Oh, yes, I'll have an iced Americano, too.

141
00:11:26,299 --> 00:11:28,217
- Yeah.
- Okay.

142
00:11:30,258 --> 00:11:33,474
What a beautiful day.

143
00:11:34,174 --> 00:11:35,674
By the way,

144
00:11:35,674 --> 00:11:38,216
were you out and about?

145
00:11:38,216 --> 00:11:41,091
- Excuse me?
- You look like you went out.

146
00:11:41,091 --> 00:11:44,799
No way, I literally just rolled out of bed.

147
00:11:46,091 --> 00:11:48,258
It's just, your whole...

148
00:11:48,258 --> 00:11:50,592
You're glowing.

149
00:11:54,885 --> 00:11:57,000
I told you not to do this!

150
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:58,049
What's my crime here?

151
00:11:58,049 --> 00:12:01,174
The rule is to always look dead tired
around the editor!

152
00:12:01,174 --> 00:12:03,716
That's Writer 101, don't you know that?

153
00:12:03,716 --> 00:12:05,299
Looking at that glow,

154
00:12:05,299 --> 00:12:09,091
the writing must be coming along great.

155
00:12:09,091 --> 00:12:11,792
That's strange, not really though.

156
00:12:11,792 --> 00:12:14,341
Maybe I just got a really good night's rest.

157
00:12:14,341 --> 00:12:16,250
Busan water must agree with you.

158
00:12:16,250 --> 00:12:18,091
I even hit the sauna this morning.

159
00:12:18,091 --> 00:12:19,924
Can't you see the glow on me?

160
00:12:19,924 --> 00:12:22,167
You're practically shining!

161
00:12:22,167 --> 00:12:24,050
Gosh.

162
00:12:27,093 --> 00:12:30,341
By the way, I heard you shared

163
00:12:30,341 --> 00:12:31,799
a room with PD Shin.

164
00:12:31,799 --> 00:12:34,875
Right, well,
I tried but he said he's sleeping in.

165
00:12:34,875 --> 00:12:37,333
So no breakfast for him.

166
00:12:37,333 --> 00:12:41,299
That guy's secretly nocturnal.
He almost never does mornings.

167
00:12:41,299 --> 00:12:44,008
Is that so?

168
00:12:44,008 --> 00:12:45,141
Then, I'll go grab...

169
00:12:45,141 --> 00:12:47,049
Oh, right!

170
00:12:47,049 --> 00:12:49,841
You should try the sushi.

171
00:12:49,841 --> 00:12:51,633
Okay.

172
00:12:58,750 --> 00:13:02,154
<i>Wasted a cute outfit for this.</i>

173
00:13:02,154 --> 00:13:04,167
<i>Since PD Shin's a no-show,</i>

174
00:13:04,167 --> 00:13:07,800
<i>let's stuff our faces.</i>

175
00:13:09,591 --> 00:13:11,425
Writer Kim,

176
00:13:13,424 --> 00:13:15,633
did you sleep well?

177
00:13:19,841 --> 00:13:21,341
It's PD Shin!

178
00:13:21,341 --> 00:13:23,292
Good thing she dressed cute just in case.

179
00:13:23,292 --> 00:13:25,466
My gosh!

180
00:13:25,466 --> 00:13:27,508
Look at that messy hair!

181
00:13:27,508 --> 00:13:30,708
That T-shirt's so effortless. Nice taste.

182
00:13:30,708 --> 00:13:34,008
He literally just woke up.
Why is everyone losing it?

183
00:13:39,792 --> 00:13:42,467
Big sushi fan, Writer Kim?

184
00:13:43,591 --> 00:13:47,841
Oh, it's just because the editor said
the sushi here was great.

185
00:13:47,841 --> 00:13:49,091
I see.

186
00:13:49,091 --> 00:13:52,758
But I don't really like sushi.

187
00:14:07,091 --> 00:14:11,008
<i>He's a sausage guy, huh.</i>

188
00:14:11,008 --> 00:14:12,799
<i>He likes chicken too?</i>

189
00:14:12,799 --> 00:14:14,958
<i>He doesn't eat vegetables.</i>

190
00:14:14,958 --> 00:14:18,091
<i>Total kid's taste buds.</i>

191
00:14:18,091 --> 00:14:20,849
<i>Even what he eats is adorable.</i>

192
00:14:28,049 --> 00:14:30,425
How's the chicken?

193
00:14:35,924 --> 00:14:37,758
Have some.

194
00:14:40,417 --> 00:14:42,508
<i>Even the short replies are cute.</i>

195
00:14:42,508 --> 00:14:45,217
<i>Why is he so adorable?</i>

196
00:14:49,466 --> 00:14:50,833
- Got it?
- Yeah.

197
00:14:50,833 --> 00:14:52,717
Go get them.

198
00:15:00,258 --> 00:15:02,000
Where's he headed?

199
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:03,875
Oh, to pick up some sandwiches.

200
00:15:03,875 --> 00:15:06,258
A few people didn't eat this morning.

201
00:15:06,258 --> 00:15:08,042
They'll all be up late,

202
00:15:08,042 --> 00:15:10,250
so it's free time until we eat lunch.

203
00:15:10,250 --> 00:15:12,133
Sure, sounds good.

204
00:15:13,758 --> 00:15:15,833
Any plans, Writer Kim?

205
00:15:15,833 --> 00:15:18,633
I might go for a little walk.

206
00:15:18,633 --> 00:15:20,583
Since I only arrived last night,

207
00:15:20,583 --> 00:15:22,375
I haven't really seen anything yet.

208
00:15:22,375 --> 00:15:23,417
That's a great idea.

209
00:15:23,417 --> 00:15:25,924
Make sure you soak up this ocean view.

210
00:15:25,924 --> 00:15:26,966
- Will do.
- Yeah.

211
00:15:26,966 --> 00:15:28,375
I'll be taking a nap.

212
00:15:28,375 --> 00:15:30,383
Sure, get some sleep.

213
00:15:49,167 --> 00:15:51,917
<i>We lost him.</i>

214
00:15:51,917 --> 00:15:54,967
<i>He can't be far. Keep looking.</i>

215
00:16:18,841 --> 00:16:21,300
<i>There he is! PD Shin!</i>

216
00:16:26,466 --> 00:16:28,424
There you are.

217
00:16:28,424 --> 00:16:30,008
Oh, Writer Kim.

218
00:16:30,008 --> 00:16:33,592
I figured I'd get coffee and take a walk.

219
00:16:34,625 --> 00:16:35,633
What would you like?

220
00:16:35,633 --> 00:16:37,091
- Let me...
- Don't worry about it.

221
00:16:37,091 --> 00:16:39,049
This is all for the writers.

222
00:16:39,049 --> 00:16:41,424
What would you like?

223
00:16:41,424 --> 00:16:43,758
Well, in that case...

224
00:16:43,758 --> 00:16:46,424
an Americano, not too strong.

225
00:16:46,424 --> 00:16:49,383
Can I add a weak Americano?

226
00:16:49,383 --> 00:16:53,183
<i>Nice! That was so natural.</i>

227
00:17:00,667 --> 00:17:02,508
That gift you sent me...

228
00:17:02,508 --> 00:17:06,633
- Oh, right.
- It turns out that cafe has the best view.

229
00:17:06,633 --> 00:17:08,917
Right over there.

230
00:17:08,917 --> 00:17:11,124
Before I leave for Seoul, I'll stop there.

231
00:17:11,124 --> 00:17:12,458
<i>While we're at it,</i>

232
00:17:12,458 --> 00:17:16,466
<i>how about we go grab one together?</i>

233
00:17:16,466 --> 00:17:17,966
Heading out for a walk, right?

234
00:17:17,966 --> 00:17:20,383
- Yes.
- Let me share a walking route.

235
00:17:20,383 --> 00:17:22,799
A really nice path came up last night.

236
00:17:22,799 --> 00:17:25,091
Are night walks your thing?

237
00:17:25,091 --> 00:17:26,258
Definitely.

238
00:17:26,258 --> 00:17:29,174
The beach at night is even better.

239
00:17:29,174 --> 00:17:31,383
<i>Night beaches are my favorite.</i>

240
00:17:31,383 --> 00:17:33,258
<i>How about later tonight,</i>

241
00:17:33,258 --> 00:17:35,924
<i>the two of us take a stroll?</i>

242
00:17:35,924 --> 00:17:37,716
Rudolph, your order!

243
00:17:37,716 --> 00:17:41,049
Rudolph, one cappuccino, one Americano,
and a ham cheese sandwich are up.

244
00:17:41,049 --> 00:17:42,808
They're ready.

245
00:17:44,633 --> 00:17:45,883
What?

246
00:17:45,883 --> 00:17:48,349
His nickname is Rudolph?

247
00:17:49,549 --> 00:17:51,758
Because his name is Soon Rok?

248
00:17:51,758 --> 00:17:54,383
<i>Unbelievable. Rudolph?</i>

249
00:17:54,383 --> 00:17:57,474
<i>Such a cute nickname too!</i>

250
00:18:08,299 --> 00:18:10,216
<i>In the village that morning,</i>

251
00:18:10,216 --> 00:18:13,391
<i>a reindeer named Rudolph showed up.</i>

252
00:18:18,341 --> 00:18:20,933
- Adorable!
- Adorable!

253
00:18:22,758 --> 00:18:26,833
Ridiculous, all of this.

254
00:18:26,833 --> 00:18:28,758
Yumi, get a grip!

255
00:18:28,758 --> 00:18:33,049
One emoji and you're like this at your age?

256
00:18:33,049 --> 00:18:35,433
Thank you.

257
00:18:37,174 --> 00:18:39,683
Oh, here, let me take that.

258
00:18:42,591 --> 00:18:44,966
By the way,

259
00:18:44,966 --> 00:18:47,356
when's your birthday?

260
00:18:47,356 --> 00:18:48,383
What?

261
00:18:48,383 --> 00:18:50,224
Your birthday...

262
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:54,591
Oh, my birthday?

263
00:18:54,591 --> 00:18:56,091
Yes,

264
00:18:56,091 --> 00:18:58,091
your birthday, Writer Kim.

265
00:18:58,091 --> 00:19:00,299
Don't make it sound so formal...

266
00:19:00,299 --> 00:19:01,924
Regular birthday is fine.

267
00:19:01,924 --> 00:19:05,266
But still, there's a big age gap, right?

268
00:19:08,258 --> 00:19:10,141
So, Writer Kim,

269
00:19:11,258 --> 00:19:13,099
what's your age?

270
00:19:18,625 --> 00:19:21,168
[Episode 11: The Road to More Than Friends]

271
00:19:22,341 --> 00:19:24,917
Oh, my birthday?

272
00:19:24,917 --> 00:19:25,966
Yes,

273
00:19:25,966 --> 00:19:28,258
your birthday, Writer Kim.

274
00:19:28,258 --> 00:19:30,174
Don't make it sound so formal...

275
00:19:30,174 --> 00:19:32,049
Regular birthday is fine.

276
00:19:32,049 --> 00:19:35,391
But still, there's a big age gap, right?

277
00:19:39,008 --> 00:19:40,974
So, Writer Kim,

278
00:19:41,633 --> 00:19:43,558
what's your age?

279
00:19:47,375 --> 00:19:48,500
[Birthday]

280
00:19:48,500 --> 00:19:50,223
[Age]

281
00:19:53,500 --> 00:19:55,075
[Birthday, Age]

282
00:19:57,049 --> 00:19:59,091
Hey, you all heard that, right?

283
00:19:59,091 --> 00:20:01,633
He asked when her birthday is.

284
00:20:01,633 --> 00:20:04,799
And how old she is.

285
00:20:04,799 --> 00:20:06,133
Now do you see what's going on?

286
00:20:06,133 --> 00:20:08,424
What PD Shin actually thinks of Yumi?

287
00:20:08,424 --> 00:20:09,966
Romance? Yeah, right.

288
00:20:09,966 --> 00:20:13,258
It's standard when speaking to an older writer.

289
00:20:13,258 --> 00:20:15,341
Being polite means using formal words,

290
00:20:15,341 --> 00:20:17,508
and using them that way is only right.

291
00:20:17,508 --> 00:20:20,708
Besides, PD Shin's all
about keeping things professional.

292
00:20:20,708 --> 00:20:22,341
Give me a break!

293
00:20:22,341 --> 00:20:25,141
So you think it's fine?

294
00:20:27,799 --> 00:20:31,049
That's the first time I've heard age like that.

295
00:20:31,049 --> 00:20:33,808
It's not like I'm a grandma.

296
00:20:36,216 --> 00:20:39,341
I almost asked it plainly
but something felt off about that too...

297
00:20:39,341 --> 00:20:41,508
What exactly is wrong about that?

298
00:20:41,508 --> 00:20:44,258
The gap isn't even that big.

299
00:20:45,341 --> 00:20:48,433
What's your birth year, Writer Kim?

300
00:20:49,383 --> 00:20:52,508
<i>Be bold. Just say how old you are.</i>

301
00:20:56,883 --> 00:20:58,341
Take a guess.

302
00:20:58,341 --> 00:21:01,133
I believe you're...

303
00:21:01,133 --> 00:21:03,683
born in nineteen ninety...

304
00:21:04,299 --> 00:21:06,000
So this is where you are, PD Shin.

305
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:07,609
Oh, Writer Kim.

306
00:21:09,633 --> 00:21:11,758
He's right over here.

307
00:21:13,716 --> 00:21:15,341
Saved by the bell,

308
00:21:15,341 --> 00:21:17,549
the age question went away.

309
00:21:17,549 --> 00:21:20,000
Not even able to say it? Forget it.

310
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:23,174
Romance with zero confidence? No chance.

311
00:21:23,174 --> 00:21:25,292
Can someone please make him stop?

312
00:21:25,292 --> 00:21:27,275
He's such a buzzkill, honestly!

313
00:21:30,292 --> 00:21:33,133
I arrived so late last night,
I didn't see anyone. When did you arrive?

314
00:21:33,133 --> 00:21:34,549
Around eleven for me.

315
00:21:34,549 --> 00:21:36,216
- Okay.
- Did you sleep well?

316
00:21:36,216 --> 00:21:39,974
Not really, I was up drinking way too late.

317
00:21:41,549 --> 00:21:45,049
You know her, right? This is Writer Kim Yumi.

318
00:21:45,049 --> 00:21:47,133
Of course, I know her.

319
00:21:47,133 --> 00:21:48,299
Nice to meet you.

320
00:21:48,299 --> 00:21:49,458
Oh, hi.

321
00:21:49,458 --> 00:21:50,966
This is Writer Kim Ju Ho,

322
00:21:50,966 --> 00:21:52,674
who writes "Invincible Baseball."

323
00:21:52,674 --> 00:21:55,466
- Hello.
- Such a pleasure, really.

324
00:21:55,466 --> 00:21:58,258
Seeing you in photos is one thing,
but face to face,

325
00:21:58,258 --> 00:22:00,208
you're absolutely stunning.

326
00:22:00,208 --> 00:22:01,958
Oh, that's so kind.

327
00:22:01,958 --> 00:22:04,258
I really mean it, that's no empty line.

328
00:22:04,258 --> 00:22:07,417
I've been dying to meet you too.

329
00:22:07,417 --> 00:22:11,174
"Invincible Baseball" is crazy popular.

330
00:22:11,174 --> 00:22:13,758
That's ancient history, time to retire it.

331
00:22:13,758 --> 00:22:15,716
It's long past due for an ending,

332
00:22:15,716 --> 00:22:18,049
but bills don't pay themselves, so here I am.

333
00:22:18,049 --> 00:22:19,549
Would you like some coffee?

334
00:22:19,549 --> 00:22:21,049
Yeah, iced Americano for me.

335
00:22:21,049 --> 00:22:23,250
- There you are.
- Grabbing a coffee?

336
00:22:23,250 --> 00:22:24,299
I'm too full for that.

337
00:22:24,299 --> 00:22:26,167
One more won't hurt, come on...

338
00:22:26,167 --> 00:22:28,383
- Two iced Americanos.
- Sure.

339
00:22:29,716 --> 00:22:32,167
Oh, Writer Kim, this is Writer Kim Ju Ho...

340
00:22:32,167 --> 00:22:33,383
I already said hi, already did.

341
00:22:33,383 --> 00:22:35,383
- Oh, you did?
- Yeah.

342
00:22:39,424 --> 00:22:42,216
PD Shin handles this team, you know.

343
00:22:42,216 --> 00:22:43,341
Oh, I see.

344
00:22:43,341 --> 00:22:46,000
Yeah, you've been wearing PD Shin out,

345
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:48,883
so I ended up taking him off her team.

346
00:22:48,883 --> 00:22:49,924
Oh, really?

347
00:22:49,924 --> 00:22:52,633
Yeah, you need to apologize for this.

348
00:22:52,633 --> 00:22:55,797
Writer Kim is already swamped
and you took her PD.

349
00:22:55,797 --> 00:22:56,841
Hold on...

350
00:22:56,841 --> 00:22:58,583
You can have him back.

351
00:22:58,583 --> 00:23:00,466
If you need him, just say the word.

352
00:23:00,466 --> 00:23:02,799
Your manuscript comes first.

353
00:23:02,799 --> 00:23:04,875
- Are you serious?
- Absolutely.

354
00:23:04,875 --> 00:23:05,884
Honestly,

355
00:23:05,884 --> 00:23:09,800
after all these years of writing,
I could do it in my sleep.

356
00:23:12,117 --> 00:23:15,799
- Bring him back!
- Bring him back!

357
00:23:15,799 --> 00:23:16,983
Then maybe...

358
00:23:16,983 --> 00:23:18,258
Writer Kim,

359
00:23:18,258 --> 00:23:19,716
don't buy a word of it.

360
00:23:19,716 --> 00:23:22,883
Without a deadline, he plays nice.

361
00:23:22,883 --> 00:23:24,133
But once deadline hits,

362
00:23:24,133 --> 00:23:27,875
he makes the biggest scene about his PD Shin.

363
00:23:27,875 --> 00:23:30,445
Seriously, really now,

364
00:23:30,445 --> 00:23:31,458
nailed it.

365
00:23:31,458 --> 00:23:33,633
Stop with that, please.

366
00:23:33,633 --> 00:23:36,008
- What's up with this guy?
- What's up with this guy?

367
00:23:40,591 --> 00:23:43,250
Honestly, PD Shin is the best.

368
00:23:43,250 --> 00:23:44,299
Thanks.

369
00:23:44,299 --> 00:23:47,674
Do you secretly dislike me?

370
00:23:47,674 --> 00:23:49,425
Here you go.

371
00:23:54,049 --> 00:23:55,625
His moods are all over the place,

372
00:23:55,625 --> 00:23:57,966
so it takes patience to put up with him.

373
00:23:57,966 --> 00:24:00,750
Come on, catering to anyone
isn't PD Shin's style.

374
00:24:00,750 --> 00:24:02,208
He stays in his own lane.

375
00:24:02,208 --> 00:24:03,708
Just keeps his head down and works.

376
00:24:03,708 --> 00:24:05,049
See for yourself.

377
00:24:05,049 --> 00:24:08,799
That right there is what makes him great.

378
00:24:08,799 --> 00:24:10,958
He's got real spine, that guy.

379
00:24:10,958 --> 00:24:12,250
- Editor.
- Yeah.

380
00:24:12,250 --> 00:24:14,383
Ten more minutes.
Everyone's waiting down in the lobby.

381
00:24:14,383 --> 00:24:15,591
Alright, got it.

382
00:24:15,591 --> 00:24:18,050
Ten minutes till we move out.

383
00:24:19,174 --> 00:24:22,663
Now it makes sense
why he's stone-faced on the job.

384
00:24:23,375 --> 00:24:26,092
I want to steal PD Shin back!

385
00:24:28,924 --> 00:24:31,716
Oh, by the way, Writer Kim...

386
00:24:31,716 --> 00:24:33,466
you said you went to the same university?

387
00:24:33,466 --> 00:24:34,841
Right?

388
00:24:34,841 --> 00:24:38,091
Yeah, that's right. Our years overlapped a bit.

389
00:24:38,091 --> 00:24:39,508
So surprisingly,

390
00:24:39,508 --> 00:24:41,571
you might be our age after all?

391
00:24:41,571 --> 00:24:44,375
Don't mind me asking,
what was your college year?

392
00:24:44,375 --> 00:24:45,375
Excuse me?

393
00:24:45,375 --> 00:24:47,250
Oh no.

394
00:24:47,250 --> 00:24:49,583
It was all going well, why that question?

395
00:24:49,583 --> 00:24:52,174
Change the subject! Change it now!

396
00:24:52,174 --> 00:24:55,252
I didn't even know we went to the same school.

397
00:24:55,252 --> 00:24:57,841
Only found out once I joined the publisher...

398
00:24:57,841 --> 00:25:01,625
Look at that bread, it's calling my name,
maybe grab some?

399
00:25:01,625 --> 00:25:06,625
I came back from the army
when she was just starting school,

400
00:25:06,625 --> 00:25:08,292
so there's three years between us.

401
00:25:08,292 --> 00:25:09,750
So that means

402
00:25:09,750 --> 00:25:11,758
you and I are only four years apart?

403
00:25:11,758 --> 00:25:13,666
That's right.

404
00:25:14,341 --> 00:25:17,685
For someone with such a baby face,
you're actually,

405
00:25:17,685 --> 00:25:18,833
quite a bit older than I guessed.

406
00:25:18,833 --> 00:25:21,466
- Oh, come on.
- What?

407
00:25:21,466 --> 00:25:25,217
Why don't the three of us be friends?

408
00:25:26,216 --> 00:25:27,466
Sorry?

409
00:25:27,466 --> 00:25:29,924
Four years apart
and he calls it friends? Please.

410
00:25:29,924 --> 00:25:32,008
Is he out of his mind?

411
00:25:32,008 --> 00:25:34,224
Forget that, check it out!

412
00:25:36,083 --> 00:25:40,425
He's literally doing the math on Yumi's age!

413
00:25:57,083 --> 00:26:00,341
The guy won't shut up.

414
00:26:00,341 --> 00:26:02,883
He's completely draining me.

415
00:26:02,883 --> 00:26:06,016
There's a real age gap here.

416
00:26:07,008 --> 00:26:09,516
True, that's a fact.

417
00:26:10,549 --> 00:26:12,974
Alright, fine, I'll own it.

418
00:26:15,167 --> 00:26:17,779
Is there even a chance here?

419
00:26:19,174 --> 00:26:22,883
Not even all my fingers could cover it.

420
00:26:27,549 --> 00:26:29,549
Don't fall asleep, Yumi!

421
00:26:29,549 --> 00:26:32,016
No time to sleep!

422
00:26:32,958 --> 00:26:35,508
What was the whole point of coming to Busan?

423
00:26:37,549 --> 00:26:40,417
Giving up now isn't an option.

424
00:26:40,417 --> 00:26:41,966
Love Cell.

425
00:26:41,966 --> 00:26:44,349
Didn't you know he's younger?

426
00:26:45,466 --> 00:26:47,508
Did you really not know?

427
00:26:48,341 --> 00:26:49,841
Our Yumi

428
00:26:49,841 --> 00:26:52,708
is way past the rookie stage.

429
00:26:52,708 --> 00:26:54,633
That's right, Yumi's the real deal!

430
00:26:54,633 --> 00:26:55,883
Sure, the years have added up,

431
00:26:55,883 --> 00:26:57,966
but that brings experience and wisdom.

432
00:26:57,966 --> 00:26:59,299
Plus...

433
00:26:59,299 --> 00:27:01,883
Her skin is flawless.

434
00:27:07,799 --> 00:27:10,667
Whatever happens between you and PD Shin today,

435
00:27:10,667 --> 00:27:12,167
it could be the start of something.

436
00:27:12,167 --> 00:27:14,466
- Yeah, no doubt.
- We've still got a shot!

437
00:27:14,466 --> 00:27:15,708
Be confident!

438
00:27:15,708 --> 00:27:17,299
Onward, to romance!

439
00:27:17,299 --> 00:27:20,058
- Onward, to romance!
- Onward, to romance!

440
00:27:22,917 --> 00:27:26,083
Should I text him after the meeting
and ask what he's doing?

441
00:27:43,674 --> 00:27:44,716
Hello?

442
00:27:44,716 --> 00:27:47,883
<i>Hi, Writer Kim, it's Kim Ju Ho.</i>

443
00:27:47,883 --> 00:27:49,516
Yes?

444
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:52,049
Right, hi.

445
00:27:52,049 --> 00:27:54,549
What are you up to right now?

446
00:27:54,549 --> 00:27:56,266
Me?

447
00:27:57,674 --> 00:27:59,891
I'm not really doing anything.

448
00:28:01,091 --> 00:28:04,341
So here's the thing, lunch isn't until one,

449
00:28:04,341 --> 00:28:06,049
and we've got time to kill.

450
00:28:06,049 --> 00:28:07,341
I was thinking of swinging by

451
00:28:07,341 --> 00:28:10,174
Bosu-dong Book Street, kind of a work thing.

452
00:28:10,174 --> 00:28:11,716
Want to tag along?

453
00:28:11,716 --> 00:28:14,091
Bosu-dong Book Street?

454
00:28:14,091 --> 00:28:18,091
Yeah, a quick cab ride there and back,
timing's perfect.

455
00:28:18,091 --> 00:28:19,966
Come with me, just to look around.

456
00:28:19,966 --> 00:28:21,383
<i>The place is packed with books.</i>

457
00:28:21,383 --> 00:28:24,712
<i>I guarantee you'll love it.</i>

458
00:28:24,712 --> 00:28:27,216
I'm not sure, I don't really...

459
00:28:27,216 --> 00:28:28,549
<i>Hey, PD Shin,</i>

460
00:28:28,549 --> 00:28:31,208
<i>two hours is enough
to look around and head back, right?</i>

461
00:28:31,208 --> 00:28:33,966
<i>Yeah, two hours works fine.</i>

462
00:28:33,966 --> 00:28:35,174
- What?
- What?

463
00:28:35,174 --> 00:28:37,674
Soon Rok's going too?

464
00:28:37,674 --> 00:28:40,841
So if I'm going, who else is in?

465
00:28:40,841 --> 00:28:44,224
It'll just be me and PD Shin.

466
00:28:45,383 --> 00:28:49,208
Dae Yong's tied up with something, so he's out.

467
00:28:49,208 --> 00:28:51,716
All right.

468
00:28:51,716 --> 00:28:53,341
Let's go!

469
00:28:53,341 --> 00:28:55,049
Come on, just come with us.

470
00:28:55,049 --> 00:28:57,841
You might pick up
some inspiration for your writing.

471
00:28:57,841 --> 00:29:00,558
- Who's that on the phone?
- Writer Kim Yumi.

472
00:29:02,966 --> 00:29:05,549
Okay, sure,

473
00:29:05,549 --> 00:29:07,674
I guess I'll join you.

474
00:29:07,674 --> 00:29:10,091
I've got nothing going on,

475
00:29:10,091 --> 00:29:13,183
and I've been curious about Bosu-dong anyway.

476
00:29:15,458 --> 00:29:18,758
Perfect, meet you in the lobby in ten.

477
00:29:18,758 --> 00:29:20,391
Sounds good.

478
00:29:32,258 --> 00:29:33,549
Yes!

479
00:29:33,549 --> 00:29:35,299
We just keep running into each other naturally.

480
00:29:35,299 --> 00:29:37,924
Still, Writer Kim tagging along
is throwing me off.

481
00:29:37,924 --> 00:29:40,883
Having someone else around
actually keeps it casual.

482
00:29:40,883 --> 00:29:42,174
When you're in that more-than-friends zone,

483
00:29:42,174 --> 00:29:44,216
a third person is essential.

484
00:29:44,216 --> 00:29:45,924
Knew it!

485
00:29:45,924 --> 00:29:49,008
- Experience and wisdom!
- Experience and wisdom!

486
00:29:49,008 --> 00:29:50,633
PD Shin, we need to book a cab.

487
00:29:50,633 --> 00:29:52,974
Already on it, calling one now.

488
00:29:53,758 --> 00:29:55,192
- She said yes.
- No kidding?

489
00:29:56,458 --> 00:29:59,417
Hey, you're positive
Writer Yumi's single, right?

490
00:29:59,417 --> 00:30:03,758
Single, totally single.
She's my wife's best friend, I'd know.

491
00:30:03,758 --> 00:30:06,633
Okay, got it.

492
00:30:10,083 --> 00:30:11,216
Hang on a second.

493
00:30:11,216 --> 00:30:12,549
Hey, hang on to the cab.

494
00:30:12,549 --> 00:30:15,174
- What's up?
- I need to run up to my room for a second.

495
00:30:15,174 --> 00:30:18,717
- Good luck out there.
- Yeah, I'll see you later.

496
00:30:29,508 --> 00:30:31,758
Hi, PD Shin.

497
00:30:31,758 --> 00:30:33,716
Hey, Writer.

498
00:30:33,716 --> 00:30:35,799
- Where did Writer Kim go...
- He ran to grab his camera.

499
00:30:35,799 --> 00:30:37,800
He'll be right down.

500
00:30:40,299 --> 00:30:42,542
Hey, you're not wiped out?

501
00:30:42,542 --> 00:30:43,591
Sorry?

502
00:30:43,591 --> 00:30:46,758
You got in super late last night
and you've been going since early.

503
00:30:46,758 --> 00:30:49,841
If you're beat,
you really don't need to push yourself to come.

504
00:30:49,841 --> 00:30:52,091
No, really, I'm good.

505
00:30:52,091 --> 00:30:53,924
If you only said yes
because you felt bad saying no,

506
00:30:53,924 --> 00:30:56,008
I can smooth it over with Writer Kim.

507
00:30:56,008 --> 00:30:57,674
No, that's not it at all.

508
00:30:57,674 --> 00:31:00,549
I actually think it'll be good to check out.

509
00:31:00,549 --> 00:31:02,174
It might even work its way into my script.

510
00:31:02,174 --> 00:31:03,924
Oh, Busan?

511
00:31:03,924 --> 00:31:06,508
You're putting Busan in your story?

512
00:31:07,383 --> 00:31:11,049
Yeah, I think it's about to make an appearance.

513
00:31:11,049 --> 00:31:13,508
So what goes down in Busan?

514
00:31:15,549 --> 00:31:17,841
Still working it out.

515
00:31:17,841 --> 00:31:21,341
The female lead takes
a solo trip down to Busan...

516
00:31:21,341 --> 00:31:22,883
Wait, the female lead?

517
00:31:22,883 --> 00:31:25,724
The one who's scared of traveling?

518
00:31:27,341 --> 00:31:29,633
Could you lay off the questions?

519
00:31:29,633 --> 00:31:31,924
Why are you grilling me like this?

520
00:31:31,924 --> 00:31:34,549
Because I want more time with you, all right?

521
00:31:34,549 --> 00:31:37,925
Do I seriously have to say it out loud?

522
00:31:40,883 --> 00:31:44,083
Yeah, so anyway...

523
00:31:44,083 --> 00:31:46,792
Oh, the cab's here.

524
00:31:48,549 --> 00:31:51,008
Hey, PD Shin!

525
00:31:51,008 --> 00:31:53,758
Oh, hi Writer. You're here.

526
00:31:53,758 --> 00:31:56,508
- This is our ride?
- Yeah.

527
00:31:56,508 --> 00:31:58,091
Let's go.

528
00:31:58,091 --> 00:32:00,092
All right, let's go.

529
00:32:10,633 --> 00:32:14,758
Do you make it down to Busan often?

530
00:32:14,758 --> 00:32:15,924
Not really.

531
00:32:15,924 --> 00:32:20,383
I think this is only my third or fourth time.

532
00:32:20,383 --> 00:32:23,633
I was down here all the time as a kid.

533
00:32:23,633 --> 00:32:25,591
My hometown doesn't have a baseball team,

534
00:32:25,591 --> 00:32:27,466
so I grew up rooting for the Busan Cougars.

535
00:32:27,466 --> 00:32:28,508
Yeah.

536
00:32:28,508 --> 00:32:33,167
Man, I was baseball-crazy
but totally broke back then.

537
00:32:33,167 --> 00:32:34,625
Couldn't even swing a Tongil ticket.

538
00:32:34,625 --> 00:32:37,708
I was riding the Bidulgi all the way down.

539
00:32:37,708 --> 00:32:40,667
That Bidulgi ride must've taken half your life.

540
00:32:40,667 --> 00:32:41,716
Totally.

541
00:32:41,716 --> 00:32:46,008
But honestly, we'd just goof around
with the guys the whole ride.

542
00:32:48,508 --> 00:32:50,467
Knew it!

543
00:32:51,716 --> 00:32:54,716
- Sorry?
- I knew we were on the same wavelength.

544
00:32:54,716 --> 00:32:57,583
You know the Bidulgi.

545
00:32:57,583 --> 00:32:59,299
PD Shin's got no clue, right?

546
00:32:59,299 --> 00:33:01,091
You know what the Bidulgi train is?

547
00:33:01,091 --> 00:33:02,708
The Bidulgi train?

548
00:33:02,708 --> 00:33:04,750
No idea, right?

549
00:33:05,383 --> 00:33:07,391
Is it the name of a ship?

550
00:33:08,883 --> 00:33:10,083
See, what did I tell you?

551
00:33:10,083 --> 00:33:12,466
Their whole generation's got no clue.

552
00:33:12,466 --> 00:33:15,716
Seriously, we're the last ones
who actually rode the Bidulgi.

553
00:33:15,716 --> 00:33:17,591
I think it was what, around 2000?

554
00:33:17,591 --> 00:33:20,716
That's when they pulled the plug.

555
00:33:20,716 --> 00:33:22,842
See, we're on the same page.

556
00:33:24,716 --> 00:33:27,500
Come on, same team, right?

557
00:33:27,500 --> 00:33:29,425
Friends.

558
00:33:30,174 --> 00:33:32,383
The Bidulgi train?

559
00:33:32,383 --> 00:33:36,049
Seriously, we grew up in the same era.

560
00:33:36,049 --> 00:33:38,425
Not really, though.

561
00:33:39,341 --> 00:33:40,508
Gosh.

562
00:33:40,508 --> 00:33:42,708
That writer is seriously getting on my nerves.

563
00:33:42,708 --> 00:33:45,083
Why does he keep acting
like we're from the same generation?

564
00:33:45,083 --> 00:33:46,841
And right in front of Soon Rok of all people!

565
00:33:46,841 --> 00:33:48,424
We can't let this slide.

566
00:33:48,424 --> 00:33:51,341
Next time he pulls out some old reference,
let's just ignore it.

567
00:33:51,341 --> 00:33:53,091
Guys...

568
00:33:53,091 --> 00:33:54,799
we're in trouble.

569
00:33:54,799 --> 00:33:55,883
What's wrong?

570
00:33:55,883 --> 00:33:58,841
The place we just walked into

571
00:33:58,841 --> 00:34:02,101
is a nostalgia paradise.

572
00:34:09,382 --> 00:34:11,583
Here we are, Bosu-dong Book Street.

573
00:34:11,583 --> 00:34:14,758
[Jane Bookstore]
This shop's packed with books too.

574
00:34:20,500 --> 00:34:22,833
This place is incredible.

575
00:34:24,633 --> 00:34:28,099
Oh, old magazines.

576
00:34:29,216 --> 00:34:31,216
Oh, no way, it's Gukjjin Bread.

577
00:34:31,216 --> 00:34:32,758
Writer Kim.

578
00:34:32,758 --> 00:34:35,458
You remember this, right? Gukjjin Bread.

579
00:34:35,458 --> 00:34:38,042
I was obsessed
with Gukjjin Bread back in the day.

580
00:34:38,042 --> 00:34:39,091
You know this, right?

581
00:34:39,091 --> 00:34:42,299
We'd save the stickers
and throw out the bread?

582
00:34:42,299 --> 00:34:43,883
<i>I remember.</i>

583
00:34:43,883 --> 00:34:46,383
<i>I must've bought a hundred
just for the stickers.</i>

584
00:34:46,383 --> 00:34:49,125
<i>And it was always
the same sticker every single time.</i>

585
00:34:49,125 --> 00:34:52,133
Wait, PD Shin, do you even recognize this?

586
00:34:53,008 --> 00:34:56,425
Never seen it before.
Is this bread made by Kim Guk Jin or something?

587
00:34:58,383 --> 00:35:00,049
Made by Kim Guk Jin...

588
00:35:00,049 --> 00:35:02,292
See, what did I say, he has no idea.

589
00:35:02,292 --> 00:35:05,250
Their generation's
completely different from ours.

590
00:35:05,250 --> 00:35:07,000
Honestly,

591
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:08,750
I don't know what it is either.

592
00:35:08,750 --> 00:35:11,549
What? There's no way you wouldn't know this.

593
00:35:11,549 --> 00:35:14,708
No, I really don't...

594
00:35:14,708 --> 00:35:17,549
Must've been before my time.

595
00:35:17,549 --> 00:35:19,424
Come on, we're the same generation.

596
00:35:19,424 --> 00:35:20,883
We're not, actually.

597
00:35:20,883 --> 00:35:23,383
We're really not.

598
00:35:25,008 --> 00:35:26,335
Come on.

599
00:35:26,335 --> 00:35:27,958
We're from the same era, right?

600
00:35:27,958 --> 00:35:29,875
Writer!

601
00:35:31,875 --> 00:35:33,708
Let's do a quick loop and get out of here.

602
00:35:33,708 --> 00:35:35,000
If we stay any longer,

603
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:38,092
we'll never escape
this generation-bonding nightmare!

604
00:35:52,216 --> 00:35:55,716
<i>This street is actually pretty great.
The atmosphere's lovely.</i>

605
00:35:55,716 --> 00:36:00,217
<i>How great would it be to come here
with just Soon Rok?</i>

606
00:36:04,674 --> 00:36:07,133
<i>Speaking of Soon Rok, where is he?</i>

607
00:36:22,341 --> 00:36:24,958
You definitely know this one, right?

608
00:36:24,958 --> 00:36:26,591
[That Guy Was Cool]
Guiyeoni.

609
00:36:26,591 --> 00:36:28,674
They've got this book here.

610
00:36:28,674 --> 00:36:30,758
Honestly, Guiyeoni's

611
00:36:30,758 --> 00:36:34,299
practically a legend to writers like us.

612
00:36:34,299 --> 00:36:37,258
I don't really know much about that.

613
00:36:37,258 --> 00:36:39,174
Oh, stop pretending, no way you don't know.

614
00:36:39,174 --> 00:36:42,466
I'm telling you, we're different generations.

615
00:36:42,466 --> 00:36:45,667
By the way, where did PD Shin disappear to?

616
00:36:45,667 --> 00:36:47,592
I can't see him anywhere.

617
00:36:48,674 --> 00:36:51,383
He already took off.

618
00:36:51,383 --> 00:36:52,750
What? Where did...

619
00:36:52,750 --> 00:36:56,300
He had something to take care of,
so he left early.

620
00:36:57,424 --> 00:37:00,500
- But...
- I bet you're starving.

621
00:37:00,500 --> 00:37:04,717
Want to grab something quick
to eat around here?

622
00:37:25,189 --> 00:37:26,231
Hello?

623
00:37:26,231 --> 00:37:27,249
<i>Where are you?</i>

624
00:37:27,249 --> 00:37:28,966
I'm heading back to the hotel.

625
00:37:28,966 --> 00:37:30,174
All three of you?

626
00:37:30,174 --> 00:37:33,258
No, just me.

627
00:37:33,258 --> 00:37:34,716
Just you?

628
00:37:34,716 --> 00:37:37,674
He told me to go ahead.

629
00:37:37,674 --> 00:37:40,008
Unreal, that guy, I swear.

630
00:37:40,008 --> 00:37:41,925
All right.

631
00:38:08,674 --> 00:38:11,883
Hello, I Da.

632
00:38:11,883 --> 00:38:14,424
<i>What's up?</i>

633
00:38:14,424 --> 00:38:16,876
You resting okay? Having fun over there?

634
00:38:16,876 --> 00:38:19,699
Fun? I'm dead tired.

635
00:38:21,019 --> 00:38:24,008
You met this writer Kim Ju Ho, right?

636
00:38:24,008 --> 00:38:26,133
<i>So, what's he like?</i>

637
00:38:26,133 --> 00:38:27,222
What do you mean?

638
00:38:27,222 --> 00:38:30,633
My husband said the guy's a huge fan of yours.

639
00:38:30,633 --> 00:38:31,833
[Yumi]
Apparently he's been begging

640
00:38:31,833 --> 00:38:33,216
to be introduced to you for ages.

641
00:38:33,216 --> 00:38:35,417
- So you ran into him there, right?
- Yeah, I did.

642
00:38:35,417 --> 00:38:36,549
So what do you think?

643
00:38:36,549 --> 00:38:40,133
I've seen him around, he's funny,
seems like a really decent guy.

644
00:38:40,133 --> 00:38:42,049
Did you all plan this together or what?

645
00:38:42,049 --> 00:38:43,591
- What?
<i>- You all teamed up</i>

646
00:38:43,591 --> 00:38:46,341
to set me up with him, didn't you?

647
00:38:46,341 --> 00:38:48,883
He drags me along saying it's for research,

648
00:38:48,883 --> 00:38:52,133
and the next thing I know,
the PD vanishes without saying anything.

649
00:38:52,133 --> 00:38:53,333
- No way.
<i>- So</i>

650
00:38:53,333 --> 00:38:56,760
the two of us ended up having lunch
and coffee together. On our very first meeting.

651
00:38:56,760 --> 00:38:57,799
Like a date.

652
00:38:57,799 --> 00:38:59,713
Really?

653
00:38:59,713 --> 00:39:01,119
You did?

654
00:39:01,119 --> 00:39:02,208
<i>Just the two of you alone?</i>

655
00:39:02,208 --> 00:39:04,966
Why is everyone so desperate to pair me off?

656
00:39:04,966 --> 00:39:07,542
Oh, come on. That's not it at all.

657
00:39:07,542 --> 00:39:09,966
He makes good money,

658
00:39:09,966 --> 00:39:11,466
he's the right age,

659
00:39:11,466 --> 00:39:14,591
and you're both in the same line of work,
so you'd probably understand each other.

660
00:39:14,591 --> 00:39:17,383
<i>That's the whole point.</i>

661
00:39:17,383 --> 00:39:19,500
I see.

662
00:39:19,500 --> 00:39:21,341
Right age, sure...

663
00:39:21,341 --> 00:39:22,674
<i>You guys click in a lot of ways.</i>

664
00:39:22,674 --> 00:39:24,008
<i>Oh, sweetie.</i>

665
00:39:24,008 --> 00:39:26,508
So because we match up so well,

666
00:39:26,508 --> 00:39:28,508
the PD just conveniently disappeared.

667
00:39:28,508 --> 00:39:30,758
That was the whole setup.

668
00:39:30,758 --> 00:39:32,792
So, you don't like him?

669
00:39:32,792 --> 00:39:36,424
It's not that I don't like him.

670
00:39:36,424 --> 00:39:37,716
No.

671
00:39:37,716 --> 00:39:41,883
Who am I to say whether I like him or not?

672
00:39:41,883 --> 00:39:43,258
That's not it at all.

673
00:39:43,258 --> 00:39:45,359
Okay.

674
00:39:51,216 --> 00:39:54,258
Why did I even bother
coming all the way to Busan?

675
00:39:54,258 --> 00:39:56,383
This is unbelievable.

676
00:40:06,258 --> 00:40:07,799
Hi, PD Jang.

677
00:40:07,799 --> 00:40:10,841
<i>Writer, I haven't seen you all day.</i>

678
00:40:10,841 --> 00:40:13,049
I know, I've been pretty busy.

679
00:40:13,049 --> 00:40:14,424
<i>Meet me down in the lobby.</i>

680
00:40:14,424 --> 00:40:16,258
<i>We're heading out for dinner soon.</i>

681
00:40:16,258 --> 00:40:18,717
Okay, sure, I'll be right there.

682
00:40:26,716 --> 00:40:29,092
I should at least eat something.

683
00:40:40,049 --> 00:40:42,591
They spent the whole day together
and he just got in.

684
00:40:42,591 --> 00:40:45,133
Is this thing actually happening?

685
00:40:45,133 --> 00:40:47,049
Unbelievable, are they talking about me again?

686
00:40:47,049 --> 00:40:49,174
Come on, what's wrong with everyone?

687
00:40:49,174 --> 00:40:50,292
I'm telling you,

688
00:40:50,292 --> 00:40:53,508
he is absolutely giddy.

689
00:40:53,508 --> 00:40:55,300
Is that so?

690
00:40:59,924 --> 00:41:01,216
<i>The nerve of him.</i>

691
00:41:01,216 --> 00:41:02,591
<i>Who does he think he is?</i>

692
00:41:02,591 --> 00:41:03,841
But honestly,

693
00:41:03,841 --> 00:41:06,550
don't they seem like a pretty good match?

694
00:41:10,716 --> 00:41:12,424
Not really.

695
00:41:12,424 --> 00:41:13,508
What?

696
00:41:13,508 --> 00:41:15,299
I don't think they go together that well.

697
00:41:15,299 --> 00:41:16,375
Not a match?

698
00:41:16,375 --> 00:41:18,925
Why not? I think they'd be great.

699
00:41:28,042 --> 00:41:30,794
[Episode 12: Is There Any Chance?]

700
00:41:31,508 --> 00:41:33,258
I don't think they go together that well.

701
00:41:33,258 --> 00:41:34,466
Not a match?

702
00:41:34,466 --> 00:41:36,633
Why not? I think they'd be great.

703
00:41:36,633 --> 00:41:38,674
No,

704
00:41:38,674 --> 00:41:40,592
they're not a match.

705
00:41:46,383 --> 00:41:47,799
How so? In what way?

706
00:41:47,799 --> 00:41:50,300
Which part doesn't work?

707
00:41:53,216 --> 00:41:55,758
Editor.

708
00:41:56,799 --> 00:41:58,049
Oh, you made it back.

709
00:41:58,049 --> 00:41:59,549
- Gosh.
- You're here?

710
00:41:59,549 --> 00:42:00,799
How'd the fishing go?

711
00:42:00,799 --> 00:42:03,083
- Oh, Writer Kim.
- Oh, hi, PD Jang.

712
00:42:03,083 --> 00:42:05,375
You're impossible to find, I swear.

713
00:42:05,375 --> 00:42:08,966
I've been trying to find you everywhere.

714
00:42:08,966 --> 00:42:10,375
Let me introduce you.

715
00:42:10,375 --> 00:42:11,792
This is Writer Kim Yumi,

716
00:42:11,792 --> 00:42:13,583
and this is Writer Bae Woo Ju.

717
00:42:13,583 --> 00:42:15,341
- Oh, hi, nice to meet you.
- Pleasure to meet you.

718
00:42:15,341 --> 00:42:17,542
I'm a huge fan of your work.

719
00:42:17,542 --> 00:42:19,174
Thank you.

720
00:42:19,174 --> 00:42:20,924
Looks like everyone's already over there.

721
00:42:20,924 --> 00:42:22,133
- Let's go join them.
- Sure.

722
00:42:22,133 --> 00:42:23,383
- Okay.
- Let's go.

723
00:42:23,383 --> 00:42:24,466
Hi, everyone.

724
00:42:24,466 --> 00:42:26,341
Oh, you're here?

725
00:42:26,341 --> 00:42:27,591
This is Writer Bae Woo Ju.

726
00:42:27,591 --> 00:42:29,125
Go ahead and say hi.

727
00:42:29,125 --> 00:42:31,633
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you, too.

728
00:42:58,466 --> 00:42:59,966
This place is huge.

729
00:42:59,966 --> 00:43:01,883
Right this way.

730
00:43:03,667 --> 00:43:05,174
- What about the other team?
- They're all here.

731
00:43:05,174 --> 00:43:07,175
All right, great.

732
00:43:10,966 --> 00:43:12,758
Where's the restroom?

733
00:43:12,758 --> 00:43:14,924
One floor up.

734
00:43:14,924 --> 00:43:16,508
Thanks.

735
00:43:16,508 --> 00:43:18,550
Go on in.

736
00:43:28,466 --> 00:43:30,883
<i>Coming to Busan was the right move, right?</i>

737
00:43:30,883 --> 00:43:34,342
<i>Absolutely, totally worth it.</i>

738
00:43:35,258 --> 00:43:37,258
It was worth it.

739
00:43:40,799 --> 00:43:42,674
Oh, come on.

740
00:43:42,674 --> 00:43:45,262
Oh, Writer Kim!

741
00:43:46,508 --> 00:43:48,174
Writer, over here.

742
00:43:48,174 --> 00:43:50,258
Come sit right here.

743
00:43:51,008 --> 00:43:53,508
Hold on, that spot looks like a trap.

744
00:43:53,508 --> 00:43:54,792
Oh, Writer, come on over.

745
00:43:54,792 --> 00:43:57,133
There's a seat open right here.

746
00:43:58,008 --> 00:44:00,292
<i>Careful, they're all around the same age!</i>

747
00:44:00,292 --> 00:44:02,466
- Oh no, it's fine, I'll just...
- Come on.

748
00:44:02,466 --> 00:44:03,966
Go sit further in.

749
00:44:03,966 --> 00:44:07,292
This seat's by the door
and we need to come in and out.

750
00:44:07,292 --> 00:44:08,508
Over here.

751
00:44:08,508 --> 00:44:10,466
- Yeah, right here.
- Come over here.

752
00:44:10,466 --> 00:44:13,016
Yeah, over here.

753
00:44:15,841 --> 00:44:19,217
You made it.

754
00:44:22,008 --> 00:44:25,674
This spot's yours. I held it.

755
00:44:25,674 --> 00:44:28,341
It's the seat of honor.

756
00:44:28,341 --> 00:44:29,549
I appreciate it.

757
00:44:29,549 --> 00:44:31,510
It's nice to meet you, Writer Kim.

758
00:44:31,510 --> 00:44:32,549
Nice to meet you, too.

759
00:44:32,549 --> 00:44:35,000
I'm Isabelle.

760
00:44:35,000 --> 00:44:36,716
But something's off.

761
00:44:36,716 --> 00:44:40,091
You said it's the seat of honor.

762
00:44:40,091 --> 00:44:41,758
Honor seat? No way.

763
00:44:41,758 --> 00:44:43,341
More like the senior section.

764
00:44:43,341 --> 00:44:44,674
Oh, come on.

765
00:44:46,042 --> 00:44:47,466
Bingo!

766
00:44:47,466 --> 00:44:48,758
You sit here

767
00:44:48,758 --> 00:44:52,924
if the Bidulgi train rings a bell.

768
00:44:52,924 --> 00:44:56,008
That's such nonsense.

769
00:44:56,008 --> 00:44:58,583
Kids these days have no clue
what a Bidulgi train is?

770
00:44:58,583 --> 00:44:59,792
Not a single one.

771
00:44:59,792 --> 00:45:02,842
Besides us four, nobody's heard of it.

772
00:45:07,133 --> 00:45:08,633
I can't believe this.

773
00:45:08,633 --> 00:45:11,633
Here comes the old-timer talk again!

774
00:45:11,633 --> 00:45:14,099
Is that so?

775
00:45:15,958 --> 00:45:17,583
- Good work today.
- Please, don't mention it.

776
00:45:17,583 --> 00:45:20,125
You worked hard today.

777
00:45:20,125 --> 00:45:21,133
Let's toast.

778
00:45:21,133 --> 00:45:24,092
- Great job.
- Great job.

779
00:45:31,799 --> 00:45:33,508
Your attention, please...

780
00:45:33,508 --> 00:45:35,466
Let me just

781
00:45:35,466 --> 00:45:37,841
share a few thoughts.

782
00:45:37,841 --> 00:45:40,966
Our writers are always swamped,

783
00:45:40,966 --> 00:45:43,626
so this gathering's rare.

784
00:45:43,626 --> 00:45:47,042
I'm really moved today.

785
00:45:47,042 --> 00:45:48,966
Sure, plenty of you

786
00:45:48,966 --> 00:45:51,674
are old friends here,

787
00:45:51,674 --> 00:45:54,591
but some of you haven't met,

788
00:45:54,591 --> 00:45:56,716
even at the same publisher.

789
00:45:56,716 --> 00:45:58,133
That's why

790
00:45:58,133 --> 00:46:00,299
I want to do introductions.

791
00:46:00,299 --> 00:46:03,833
Now, where do I start?

792
00:46:03,833 --> 00:46:05,841
Hey, you know what,

793
00:46:05,841 --> 00:46:07,258
let's do it by class year.

794
00:46:07,258 --> 00:46:09,633
- Have a seat.
- Sure thing.

795
00:46:09,633 --> 00:46:10,841
Okay,

796
00:46:10,841 --> 00:46:13,758
so Writer Isabelle goes first.

797
00:46:15,091 --> 00:46:17,417
Here he goes again.

798
00:46:17,417 --> 00:46:19,008
- So annoying!
- By class year,

799
00:46:19,008 --> 00:46:22,042
Yumi comes fourth!

800
00:46:22,042 --> 00:46:24,508
Seriously, me again?

801
00:46:24,508 --> 00:46:26,799
Unless we're going by looks,
I shouldn't be first.

802
00:46:26,799 --> 00:46:29,841
Are we really doing pecking order here?

803
00:46:29,841 --> 00:46:31,633
Just go with the flow.

804
00:46:31,633 --> 00:46:34,512
Yeah, freestyle all the way.

805
00:46:34,512 --> 00:46:35,583
Freestyle?

806
00:46:35,583 --> 00:46:37,341
Let me start then.

807
00:46:37,341 --> 00:46:39,070
What?

808
00:46:39,883 --> 00:46:43,841
Hi, I'm Writer Kim Yumi.

809
00:46:43,841 --> 00:46:48,183
It's really nice to meet you all.

810
00:46:53,758 --> 00:46:56,675
You're so cool.

811
00:47:07,091 --> 00:47:09,591
So you're an only child?

812
00:47:09,591 --> 00:47:11,216
Yeah, only child.

813
00:47:11,216 --> 00:47:13,591
Five kids, I'm the last.

814
00:47:13,591 --> 00:47:15,799
I've got three sisters and a brother.

815
00:47:15,799 --> 00:47:18,549
Got it.

816
00:47:18,549 --> 00:47:21,049
So from a noodle company

817
00:47:21,049 --> 00:47:23,000
to writing? How?

818
00:47:23,000 --> 00:47:25,167
My degree's in creative writing,

819
00:47:25,167 --> 00:47:28,049
and that's pretty much my only skill.

820
00:47:28,049 --> 00:47:30,841
Finance team to writing,

821
00:47:30,841 --> 00:47:34,341
that's quite the jump, right?

822
00:47:34,341 --> 00:47:36,508
That's a long one.

823
00:47:36,508 --> 00:47:39,758
Not that interesting, really.

824
00:47:39,758 --> 00:47:41,750
- Hey, Writer Kim.
- Just, yeah...

825
00:47:41,750 --> 00:47:43,924
You remember that time, right?

826
00:47:43,924 --> 00:47:46,508
Back in Daehangno after the play,

827
00:47:46,508 --> 00:47:50,799
the three of us drank together,

828
00:47:50,799 --> 00:47:52,591
on the way to my place,

829
00:47:52,591 --> 00:47:53,750
you were on all fours...

830
00:47:53,750 --> 00:47:57,466
<i>No chance. He's too far away.</i>

831
00:47:57,466 --> 00:47:59,174
<i>Today's a bust.</i>

832
00:47:59,174 --> 00:48:00,792
<i>Let's give up.</i>

833
00:48:00,792 --> 00:48:01,841
<i>Listen, guys,</i>

834
00:48:01,841 --> 00:48:04,633
<i>let's just hit the sack.</i>

835
00:48:04,633 --> 00:48:07,683
<i>Yumi's wiped out.</i>

836
00:48:08,383 --> 00:48:10,383
- I walked on two.
- No, woof woof.

837
00:48:10,383 --> 00:48:12,792
- You went full dog.
- I wasn't that...

838
00:48:12,792 --> 00:48:13,924
Hang on.

839
00:48:13,924 --> 00:48:15,917
Where are you off to?

840
00:48:15,917 --> 00:48:18,133
Just to the restroom.

841
00:48:18,133 --> 00:48:21,474
You're taking your bag there?

842
00:48:23,350 --> 00:48:27,799
You sure keep a close eye on me.

843
00:48:27,799 --> 00:48:30,258
Oh, okay, go ahead.

844
00:48:33,750 --> 00:48:37,425
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

845
00:48:44,091 --> 00:48:46,092
Writer Kim.

846
00:48:47,341 --> 00:48:49,216
Where you going?

847
00:48:49,216 --> 00:48:51,633
Well...

848
00:48:51,633 --> 00:48:53,299
Mind if I slip away?

849
00:48:53,299 --> 00:48:55,379
Heading to the hotel?

850
00:48:55,379 --> 00:48:56,424
Yeah.

851
00:48:56,424 --> 00:48:58,299
I did my greetings,

852
00:48:58,299 --> 00:49:01,508
and all that running around wore me out.

853
00:49:01,508 --> 00:49:03,549
No problem, then.

854
00:49:03,549 --> 00:49:07,508
Round two's on, looks like a long night.

855
00:49:07,508 --> 00:49:08,633
I'll walk with...

856
00:49:08,633 --> 00:49:11,508
I'm good, it's just a short walk.

857
00:49:11,508 --> 00:49:12,799
Still, though.

858
00:49:12,799 --> 00:49:14,341
Really, no.

859
00:49:14,341 --> 00:49:16,883
You'd walk back alone.

860
00:49:16,883 --> 00:49:18,299
I want to walk.

861
00:49:18,299 --> 00:49:20,630
Have fun, okay?

862
00:49:22,799 --> 00:49:24,592
Head back in.

863
00:49:31,341 --> 00:49:35,091
So close, yet so far.

864
00:49:35,091 --> 00:49:37,383
It's tough.

865
00:49:37,383 --> 00:49:39,341
No chance to lock eyes.

866
00:49:39,341 --> 00:49:41,299
He won't even glance at her.

867
00:49:41,299 --> 00:49:43,633
Yumi's not on his radar.

868
00:49:43,633 --> 00:49:45,216
The guy's on the job.

869
00:49:45,216 --> 00:49:47,716
He's strict about work and personal stuff.

870
00:49:47,716 --> 00:49:50,008
Keeping it separate?

871
00:49:50,008 --> 00:49:53,549
If it's so separate, why obey Writer Ju Ho?

872
00:49:53,549 --> 00:49:55,674
He called them a bad fit, remember?

873
00:49:55,674 --> 00:49:58,174
It's the truth, that's why he said it.

874
00:49:58,174 --> 00:49:59,341
Don't you get PD Shin?

875
00:49:59,341 --> 00:50:02,424
The guy only states facts.

876
00:50:02,424 --> 00:50:04,966
Mind zipping it for once?

877
00:50:04,966 --> 00:50:06,841
Take it down a notch yourself.

878
00:50:06,841 --> 00:50:08,549
This crush is going nowhere.

879
00:50:08,549 --> 00:50:11,841
They won't even hit the flirting stage.

880
00:50:11,841 --> 00:50:13,481
Like you'd know anything!

881
00:50:13,481 --> 00:50:17,417
Romance is Yumi's genre.

882
00:50:17,417 --> 00:50:20,375
The romance playbook, remember?

883
00:50:20,375 --> 00:50:24,641
Without a hint from him, it stays a crush.

884
00:50:26,049 --> 00:50:27,341
Pay attention.

885
00:50:27,341 --> 00:50:30,799
[Crush, Sign, Flirting]
A sign from him in the crush stage,

886
00:50:30,799 --> 00:50:32,424
and it turns into flirting.

887
00:50:32,424 --> 00:50:34,091
No sign?

888
00:50:34,091 --> 00:50:36,216
It stays a crush forever.

889
00:50:36,216 --> 00:50:37,841
A sign?

890
00:50:37,841 --> 00:50:39,716
Yes, a sign.

891
00:50:39,716 --> 00:50:41,883
Look at Writer Ju Ho.

892
00:50:41,883 --> 00:50:44,966
<i>If you're not hungry, maybe something cold?</i>

893
00:50:44,966 --> 00:50:47,768
- How he acts alone with her.
<i>- Nice and cold.</i>

894
00:50:48,716 --> 00:50:49,758
<i>Writer Kim!</i>

895
00:50:49,758 --> 00:50:51,667
Always finding a way to sit close.

896
00:50:51,667 --> 00:50:52,716
<i>Come sit over here!</i>

897
00:50:52,716 --> 00:50:55,258
<i>So you're an only child?</i>

898
00:50:55,258 --> 00:50:57,442
Interest in Yumi, lots of questions.

899
00:50:58,383 --> 00:51:01,341
That's what a sign looks like.

900
00:51:01,341 --> 00:51:03,591
The kind of thing Writer Ju Ho pulls.

901
00:51:03,591 --> 00:51:06,008
Did PD Shin ever do anything like that?

902
00:51:06,008 --> 00:51:08,831
Tell me!

903
00:51:13,841 --> 00:51:17,008
How he acts alone with her.

904
00:51:17,008 --> 00:51:20,549
<i>No, my seat is over there.</i>

905
00:51:20,549 --> 00:51:23,299
<i>They didn't have a seat next to yours.</i>

906
00:51:23,299 --> 00:51:26,234
Always finding a way to sit close.

907
00:51:27,250 --> 00:51:28,875
<i>Yes.</i>

908
00:51:28,875 --> 00:51:29,917
<i>Yes.</i>

909
00:51:29,917 --> 00:51:30,956
<i>Yes.</i>

910
00:51:30,956 --> 00:51:32,000
<i>Yes.</i>

911
00:51:32,000 --> 00:51:33,098
<i>Yes.</i>

912
00:51:33,098 --> 00:51:35,175
<i>Yeah.</i>

913
00:51:35,883 --> 00:51:39,500
Interest in Yumi, lots of questions.

914
00:51:39,500 --> 00:51:42,008
Did PD Shin pull any of this?

915
00:51:42,008 --> 00:51:44,167
Tell me, has he?

916
00:51:44,167 --> 00:51:45,258
He hasn't.

917
00:51:45,258 --> 00:51:47,466
Zero times!

918
00:51:47,466 --> 00:51:48,841
Never has.

919
00:51:48,841 --> 00:51:53,958
It means PD Shin isn't into Yumi that way.

920
00:51:53,958 --> 00:51:56,841
He just stated the fact that they don't fit.

921
00:51:56,841 --> 00:51:59,508
Basically, no shot at flirting happens...

922
00:51:59,508 --> 00:52:01,842
Writer Kim.

923
00:52:06,833 --> 00:52:09,092
PD Shin.

924
00:52:11,674 --> 00:52:14,383
PD Jang said you left alone.

925
00:52:14,383 --> 00:52:16,633
She's worried.

926
00:52:17,299 --> 00:52:19,883
I'm already here.

927
00:52:19,883 --> 00:52:21,549
I know.

928
00:52:21,549 --> 00:52:23,758
I was too late coming to you, wasn't I?

929
00:52:24,924 --> 00:52:26,591
It's just around the corner.

930
00:52:26,591 --> 00:52:29,550
Still, it's nighttime.

931
00:52:31,591 --> 00:52:33,750
This is a sign.

932
00:52:33,750 --> 00:52:35,508
It isn't a sign.

933
00:52:35,508 --> 00:52:36,799
It is a sign!

934
00:52:36,799 --> 00:52:38,808
Ask him.

935
00:52:39,924 --> 00:52:42,674
You're making that up, aren't you?

936
00:52:42,674 --> 00:52:44,008
Looking for an escape,

937
00:52:44,008 --> 00:52:47,133
so you signed up to walk me?

938
00:52:47,883 --> 00:52:49,925
Well...

939
00:52:51,258 --> 00:52:53,842
You're not wrong.

940
00:52:55,799 --> 00:52:57,758
See?

941
00:53:00,049 --> 00:53:02,625
The writers there drink a lot.

942
00:53:02,625 --> 00:53:04,966
It's a bit much.

943
00:53:04,966 --> 00:53:06,383
I understand.

944
00:53:06,383 --> 00:53:08,174
It's overwhelming.

945
00:53:08,174 --> 00:53:09,925
Yeah.

946
00:53:12,372 --> 00:53:13,758
Let's go.

947
00:53:13,758 --> 00:53:15,523
Sure.

948
00:53:23,674 --> 00:53:26,025
<i>- Going up.</i>
- Get some rest.

949
00:53:27,299 --> 00:53:28,591
You're not coming up?

950
00:53:28,591 --> 00:53:31,049
Yeah, I can't sleep.

951
00:53:31,049 --> 00:53:33,049
Doing something?

952
00:53:33,049 --> 00:53:34,549
Maybe a film.

953
00:53:34,549 --> 00:53:36,466
A theater's just nearby.

954
00:53:36,466 --> 00:53:38,125
What's playing?

955
00:53:38,125 --> 00:53:39,708
It's Thomas Game.

956
00:53:39,708 --> 00:53:42,008
James King wrote the original,
so it's on my list.

957
00:53:42,008 --> 00:53:44,917
James King's a favorite of mine.

958
00:53:44,917 --> 00:53:45,958
Yeah.

959
00:53:45,958 --> 00:53:48,466
Crowds throw me off,

960
00:53:48,466 --> 00:53:51,008
so late runs work better for me.

961
00:53:51,008 --> 00:53:54,133
Turns out tonight's the final screening.

962
00:53:56,008 --> 00:53:57,799
Sleep well, then.

963
00:53:57,799 --> 00:53:59,591
Okay, enjoy the movie.

964
00:53:59,591 --> 00:54:01,341
Thanks.

965
00:54:01,341 --> 00:54:03,967
<i>Doors closing.</i>

966
00:54:11,958 --> 00:54:15,466
Isn't this actually a sign?

967
00:54:15,466 --> 00:54:18,125
All those movie details he shared.

968
00:54:18,125 --> 00:54:19,474
No need for that, right?

969
00:54:19,474 --> 00:54:21,466
Fair point.

970
00:54:21,466 --> 00:54:23,875
He's hinting she's welcome, right?

971
00:54:23,875 --> 00:54:25,500
Try asking to come, too.

972
00:54:25,500 --> 00:54:27,591
Yumi had it on her watch list, too.

973
00:54:27,591 --> 00:54:29,417
Won't he catch on?

974
00:54:29,417 --> 00:54:32,153
What if it isn't a sign?

975
00:54:32,153 --> 00:54:35,500
Hey! It isn't a sign!

976
00:54:35,500 --> 00:54:37,799
Cowards' advice doesn't count.

977
00:54:37,799 --> 00:54:40,383
Bravery matters when the moment strikes.

978
00:54:40,383 --> 00:54:44,633
If PD Shin gave a hint, reply to it.

979
00:55:05,195 --> 00:55:06,216
Hello?

980
00:55:06,216 --> 00:55:08,226
<i>It's me.</i>

981
00:55:08,226 --> 00:55:09,758
Yes, Writer Kim.

982
00:55:09,758 --> 00:55:13,008
Did you reach the theater?

983
00:55:13,008 --> 00:55:15,133
<i>Heading there now.</i>

984
00:55:16,549 --> 00:55:20,592
Once I got here, I couldn't sleep.

985
00:55:23,008 --> 00:55:24,875
That movie,

986
00:55:24,875 --> 00:55:28,217
I wanted to see it, too.

987
00:55:29,133 --> 00:55:31,383
Want to watch together?

988
00:55:48,299 --> 00:55:50,183
I prefer

989
00:55:51,299 --> 00:55:54,349
watching alone.

990
00:56:00,208 --> 00:56:01,817
It wasn't a sign!

991
00:56:01,817 --> 00:56:04,542
I knew it!

992
00:56:04,542 --> 00:56:06,208
Hey, you idiots!

993
00:56:06,208 --> 00:56:07,520
What did I say?

994
00:56:07,520 --> 00:56:10,800
Take it back! Just take it back now!

995
00:56:16,341 --> 00:56:18,466
Right?

996
00:56:18,466 --> 00:56:21,591
Movies are better solo.

997
00:56:21,591 --> 00:56:24,841
Honestly, going out's a hassle.

998
00:56:24,841 --> 00:56:27,792
I'd probably fall asleep anyway.

999
00:56:27,792 --> 00:56:29,258
Enjoy the movie.

1000
00:56:29,258 --> 00:56:31,549
Recommend it if it's good.

1001
00:56:31,549 --> 00:56:32,633
Okay.

1002
00:56:32,633 --> 00:56:34,000
See you tomorrow.

1003
00:56:34,000 --> 00:56:36,550
See you then.

1004
00:56:41,883 --> 00:56:44,092
So embarrassing.

1005
00:56:55,583 --> 00:56:58,466
You said it was a sign.

1006
00:56:58,466 --> 00:57:00,542
Jumped the gun, I admit.

1007
00:57:00,542 --> 00:57:03,417
Experience and wisdom, my foot.

1008
00:57:03,417 --> 00:57:06,175
Keep barking up the wrong tree!

1009
00:57:09,674 --> 00:57:12,383
I'm such a mess.

1010
00:57:24,624 --> 00:57:27,633
How do relationships even start?

1011
00:57:28,341 --> 00:57:31,724
Kim Yumi, you've lost your touch.

1012
00:57:39,883 --> 00:57:41,750
What now?

1013
00:57:41,750 --> 00:57:44,796
[Writer Kim Ju Ho]

1014
00:58:10,833 --> 00:58:12,953
[Movie Tickets]

1015
00:58:17,292 --> 00:58:19,140
[Writer Kim Ju Ho]

1016
00:58:26,133 --> 00:58:27,174
Yes, Writer Kim.

1017
00:58:27,174 --> 00:58:28,591
Hey, PD Shin.

1018
00:58:28,591 --> 00:58:31,258
You left with Writer Kim, right?

1019
00:58:33,049 --> 00:58:35,724
Yes, since it's dark...

1020
00:58:36,799 --> 00:58:39,674
She's still up, right?

1021
00:58:39,674 --> 00:58:41,966
But she isn't picking up.

1022
00:58:41,966 --> 00:58:47,383
Bring Writer Kim and come here.

1023
00:58:47,383 --> 00:58:48,717
- Sorry?
<i>- Well...</i>

1024
00:58:48,717 --> 00:58:50,751
We're moving to a nice spot.

1025
00:58:50,751 --> 00:58:53,049
You know the street stall by the beach?

1026
00:58:53,049 --> 00:58:57,716
So, bring her here and hurry over.

1027
00:58:57,716 --> 00:59:00,466
She doesn't handle liquor well.

1028
00:59:00,466 --> 00:59:04,966
It's not about drinking, okay?

1029
00:59:04,966 --> 00:59:06,466
<i>Anyway,</i>

1030
00:59:06,466 --> 00:59:08,883
make sure she comes with you, all right?

1031
00:59:08,883 --> 00:59:12,217
I'll text the address.

1032
00:59:15,167 --> 00:59:19,258
Be sure to come with her.

1033
00:59:19,258 --> 00:59:21,625
She can't come.

1034
00:59:21,625 --> 00:59:22,765
What?

1035
00:59:22,765 --> 00:59:23,841
How come?

1036
00:59:23,841 --> 00:59:27,633
She said she'd watch a movie, so we came.

1037
00:59:27,633 --> 00:59:30,508
It just started, so two more hours.

1038
00:59:30,508 --> 00:59:31,799
What?

1039
00:59:31,799 --> 00:59:32,875
What movie?

1040
00:59:32,875 --> 00:59:35,383
So don't call her.

1041
00:59:35,383 --> 00:59:37,592
She won't pick up.

1042
00:59:39,591 --> 00:59:41,133
Yes.

1043
00:59:41,133 --> 00:59:43,184
Yes, understood.

1044
00:59:56,549 --> 00:59:58,258
<i>That movie,</i>

1045
00:59:58,258 --> 01:00:01,516
<i>I wanted to see it, too.</i>

1046
01:00:02,625 --> 01:00:04,925
<i>Want to watch together?</i>

1047
01:00:15,383 --> 01:00:17,799
Please count me out.

1048
01:00:17,799 --> 01:00:21,683
Just enjoy your drinks.

1049
01:00:23,223 --> 01:00:24,844
<i>Writer Kim.</i>

1050
01:00:24,844 --> 01:00:27,175
<i>Still awake?</i>

1051
01:00:31,216 --> 01:00:33,424
<i>Yeah.</i>

1052
01:00:33,424 --> 01:00:35,217
<i>Why's that?</i>

1053
01:00:49,083 --> 01:00:52,342
<i>Want to watch the movie together?</i>

1054
01:00:57,716 --> 01:01:00,625
<i>That's a sign, right?</i>

1055
01:01:00,625 --> 01:01:02,675
<i>Not a sign.</i>

1056
01:01:19,667 --> 01:01:23,000
<i>You said solo's easier.</i>

1057
01:01:33,583 --> 01:01:39,437
[Want to watch the movie together?]
[You said solo's easier]

1058
01:01:51,758 --> 01:01:54,592
<i>Want to watch the movie together?</i>

1059
01:02:33,708 --> 01:02:35,043
<i>It's still early stage.</i>

1060
01:02:35,043 --> 01:02:38,049
<i>But if it keeps growing, it becomes love.</i>

1061
01:02:38,049 --> 01:02:40,591
<i>- Hey, look behind!
- What?</i>

1062
01:02:40,591 --> 01:02:42,049
<i>Am I your type?</i>

1063
01:02:42,049 --> 01:02:43,758
<i>I'd like to pursue something serious with you.</i>

1064
01:02:43,758 --> 01:02:44,966
<i>So sad.</i>

1065
01:02:44,966 --> 01:02:48,250
<i>PD Shin gave me butterflies
for the first time in a long time...</i>

1066
01:02:48,250 --> 01:02:51,125
<i>This isn't like PD Shin at all.</i>

1067
01:02:51,125 --> 01:02:53,375
<i>What's with butting in?</i>

1068
01:02:53,375 --> 01:02:55,008
